<TITLE> RAB retrieves AK-47 from Chittagong village </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, April 20 (bdnews24.com)RAB retrieved an AK-47 rifle with 49 rounds of ammunition from Rauzan upazila in Chittagong early Sunday. Assistant superintendent of police Sheikh Shariful Islam, a RAB-7 officer, told bdnews24.com that the arms and ammo had been seized from a spot beside the Mokamipara mosque in Noapara village around 3am Sunday. Acting on a tip-off, the RAB personnel raided the area. "The miscreants fled the scene leaving the arms and ammo behind," Islam said. "Necessary legal measures are being taken in this regard," he said. bdnews24.com
